Yeah.

23:16.955 --> 23:17.196
Nope.

23:18.558 --> 23:18.898
Nope.

23:20.738 --> 23:25.525
tireless, limitless, his understanding limitless.

23:25.545 --> 23:27.628
I don't know if God gets me, huh?

23:30.452 --> 23:33.877
He gives power and strength to all who hope in him.

23:37.643 --> 23:41.248
Friends, this type of renewal, it all starts by opening your heart to Jesus.

23:41.929 --> 23:47.858
Many of you know this already, but there might be some of you in the room, you've been in a season of discouragement, and you're kind of wondering, where do I start?

23:48.866 --> 23:51.368
It starts by opening your heart to Jesus.

23:52.790 --> 24:02.819
This text assures us that this kind of personalized care, this renewal from the God of the universe is available to each person who hopes in God.

24:04.241 --> 24:08.325
And hope in God starts by placing your trust in God's Son Jesus.

24:09.566 --> 24:10.427
Have you done that yet?

24:12.909 --> 24:13.570
Have you done that yet?

24:15.351 --> 24:18.034
If not, this is your first important takeaway

24:18.178 --> 24:19.079
from this sermon today.

24:19.540 --> 24:22.543
That's your first important takeaway from this whole message today.

24:23.384 --> 24:25.867
Jesus himself said, no one comes to the Father except through me.

24:27.489 --> 24:40.305
And when you walk with Jesus and you put your hope in him, he leads you like a gentle shepherd loving on you tenderly and renewing you through the struggles and disappointments in your life.

24:40.365 --> 24:41.306
Notice I said through.

24:41.326 --> 24:47.794
For some of you today, this is where it can all begin to change.

24:49.090 --> 24:49.451
Right here.

24:51.113 --> 24:56.201
Today you can open your heart to Jesus and ask Him to be your forgiver and your leader.

24:57.463 --> 24:58.604
Today could be the day for you.

24:58.625 --> 24:59.286
We're all changes.

24:59.866 --> 25:10.983
And when you do that, the Bible tells us the spirit literally sets up his residence in you and makes you his own, embraces you, makes you his own.

25:11.003 --> 25:12.065
Then he goes to work on you.

25:13.267 --> 25:15.650
Sometimes he changes your circumstances.

25:16.432 --> 25:18.034
Sometimes he changes circumstances.

25:19.266 --> 25:21.048
But often, He changes you.

25:24.312 --> 25:29.859
He gives you everything you need so you're not fighting the battles in your own strength anymore.

25:31.882 --> 25:43.296
When you open your heart to Him, and many of you already had, let me suggest three other very practical takeaways because maybe even though you've been following Jesus for a while, you're in a hard season.

25:45.679 --> 25:48.082
And you haven't been able to break out of it.

25:48.610 --> 25:51.433
So let me suggest three practical things.

25:53.174 --> 25:54.756
Number one, remember who God is.

25:56.998 --> 26:01.342
Refocus your mind before you try to fix your situation.

26:03.244 --> 26:04.125
Here's why I say that.

26:05.846 --> 26:11.832
Notice Isaiah 40 spends far more time describing God than solving Israel's problems.

26:12.933 --> 26:13.513
Did you catch that?

26:14.534 --> 26:15.475
That's not accidental.

26:17.077 --> 26:18.418
Because here's the truth.

26:18.658 --> 26:20.981
Weariness shrinks our vision.

26:22.682 --> 26:23.063
You with me?

26:23.864 --> 26:26.026
Weariness shrinks our vision.

26:27.408 --> 26:29.149
Knowing God restores it.

26:30.731 --> 26:31.672
Oh, come on, that's good.

26:33.134 --> 26:33.935
You got social media.

26:33.955 --> 26:35.056
You need this time out.

26:35.076 --> 26:36.097
You need to post that right now.

26:37.178 --> 26:38.019
Go ahead, post that.

26:38.720 --> 26:40.982
Weariness shrinks your vision.

26:42.564 --> 26:44.306
Knowing God restores it.

26:45.762 --> 26:47.945
So here's a practice you can try this week.

26:47.965 --> 26:51.550
Spend some time this week reading through these verses, verses 12 to 31.

26:51.831 --> 26:55.937
Just make a note in your outline, read through 12 to 31, read through it slowly.

26:56.117 --> 26:58.560
I had to read it fast because we've got a whole time thing.

27:00.323 --> 27:02.586
Spend some time reading through those verses slowly.

27:03.508 --> 27:06.211
Write down every description of God you see.

27:06.973 --> 27:12.120
Creator, shepherd, everlasting, powerful, attentive, whatever you see in there.

27:12.481 --> 27:13.522
Whatever God reveals to you.

27:15.138 --> 27:22.231
Then when discouraging thoughts come, begin to intentionally replace them with one of those truths about God's character that you found.

27:23.053 --> 27:23.914
Okay, very practical.

27:24.996 --> 27:25.617
Very practical.

27:26.218 --> 27:30.146
Read through the verses, write down the scriptures, use them, replace them.

27:30.166 --> 27:36.978
Remember, your strength will not return simply because your circumstances improve.

27:39.362 --> 27:42.826
Your strength is not gonna return because your circumstances improve.

27:42.846 --> 27:45.408
Your strength returns when your vision improves.

27:47.591 --> 27:51.275
Your strength improves when your vision of God grows bigger than your circumstances.

27:51.595 --> 27:51.956
You with me?

27:52.656 --> 27:53.357
So we gotta grow it.

27:54.478 --> 27:58.943
All right, secondly, practice waiting on the Lord with bite-sized faithfulness.

28:01.005 --> 28:01.165
Right?

28:01.306 --> 28:02.827
Here's why I'm saying bite-sized.

28:03.888 --> 28:05.490
When people are exhausted,

28:06.434 --> 28:11.063
They often think they need some sort of massive, dramatic spiritual breakthrough.

28:11.103 --> 28:13.809
Whoa, I've changed.

28:19.380 --> 28:23.829
But notice Isaiah's promise is for who?

28:23.849 --> 28:28.017
Those who simply wait.

28:28.037 --> 28:28.338
Huh?

28:31.490 --> 28:34.233
God is not asking you for impressive faith.

28:34.293 --> 28:36.475
He's inviting you to dependent faith.

28:39.478 --> 28:48.608
So maybe try some bite-sized spiritual practices because that's all the energy you got in this particular season.

28:48.628 --> 28:50.770
Maybe it's a short daily prayer, something like this.

28:51.591 --> 28:52.432
This is your daily prayer.

28:53.633 --> 28:54.374
Lord, I'm tired.

28:57.117 --> 28:57.938
Be my strength.

29:00.066 --> 29:01.087
Lord, I'm tired, be my strength.

29:01.107 --> 29:02.710
You might pray that 20 times a day.

29:03.691 --> 29:04.392
Lord, I'm tired.

29:04.993 --> 29:05.634
Be my strength.

29:07.196 --> 29:08.658
Maybe read one Psalm a day.

29:10.580 --> 29:13.945
Pick a short one.

29:13.965 --> 29:14.486
It's okay.

29:15.507 --> 29:19.252
Not impressive faith, just dependent faith.

29:19.272 --> 29:21.074
Listen to worship music during your commute.

29:22.917 --> 29:23.778
Or maybe try this one.

29:23.938 --> 29:26.642
Sit quietly before God for five minutes before bed.

29:27.394 --> 29:30.058
Turn off your devices, turn off your TV, turn off all the noise.

29:30.398 --> 29:34.264
Just sit, maybe in a dark room, maybe not, maybe just sit by yourself.

29:34.284 --> 29:38.049
Silence, solitude, five minutes before bed.

29:38.069 --> 29:39.932
You don't have to think anything.

29:40.553 --> 29:41.454
You don't have to pray anything.

29:41.474 --> 29:42.676
You don't have to ask God anything.

29:44.278 --> 29:45.039
Just sit with Him.

29:46.802 --> 29:47.923
Sit with your gentle shepherd.

29:53.291 --> 29:55.314
See, the goal isn't intensity, it's connection.

29:57.922 --> 30:04.089
Lastly, just take the next step, not the whole journey.

30:05.210 --> 30:07.313
Take the next step.

30:07.333 --> 30:13.119
Remember what Isaiah said, walk and not faint, right?

30:13.139 --> 30:15.282
Run, not grow weary.

30:16.804 --> 30:18.466
Mount up with wings like eagles.

30:20.147 --> 30:21.169
See what's interesting about that?

30:21.229 --> 30:24.032
Notice it's all movement, but all at different speeds.

30:25.213 --> 30:25.874
You ever notice that?

30:27.618 --> 30:28.479
It's progression.

30:29.560 --> 30:30.462
It starts small.

30:32.384 --> 30:35.948
So what's the next faithful thing God is asking of you?

30:36.189 --> 30:38.151
God, what's the next thing you need me to do?

30:39.673 --> 30:44.419
Not tomorrow, not next month, not next week, today.

30:46.582 --> 30:51.448
Maybe it's just, make a phone call.

30:51.468 --> 30:55.553
Make a phone call, reach out to somebody to encourage them or to be encouraged.

30:55.973 --> 30:56.594
Ask them to pray.

30:57.410 --> 31:01.275
Maybe it's just one thing, that very next thing is just show up at church.

31:01.295 --> 31:01.655
You did it.

31:03.477 --> 31:03.838
You did it.

31:05.319 --> 31:08.583
Maybe decide to forgive one person.

31:09.565 --> 31:16.433
It's a long process maybe, but you're choosing to free them and you're choosing to free yourself from the poison of that resentment.

31:19.777 --> 31:21.359
Maybe it's just pray one honest prayer.

31:22.961 --> 31:24.082
Just pray one honest prayer.

31:27.298 --> 31:30.084
Remember how Jesus taught us to pray.

31:32.148 --> 31:35.555
He said, give us this day our what?

31:36.477 --> 31:36.938
Daily.

31:36.958 --> 31:40.645
Not next week, not next month.

31:41.848 --> 31:43.612
So you don't need strength for tomorrow yet.

31:43.632 --> 31:45.836
You need strength for today, yeah?

31:46.357 --> 31:46.738
Yeah?

31:50.338 --> 31:52.681
God gives strength in daily portions.

31:52.741 --> 31:59.550
And when people feel hopeless, the future feels overwhelming, but God gives strength for the next step, not the entire path.

32:00.731 --> 32:01.532
Be encouraged.

32:03.655 --> 32:07.400
Some of you came in today tired in your soul, weary.

32:08.802 --> 32:09.683
You love God.

32:09.743 --> 32:15.410
Maybe you just felt a draw to be here, but you're worn down.

32:17.858 --> 32:23.506
Please realize your weariness does not disqualify you from God's promises.

32:24.267 --> 32:26.811
The opposite, it qualifies you for them.

32:28.534 --> 32:31.398
The promises I say it gives today were not meant for the strong.

32:32.299 --> 32:32.920
You notice that?

32:32.960 --> 32:36.385
There for the weary who wait.

32:38.869 --> 32:42.074
The weary who wait.

32:42.094 --> 32:45.138
So if you're weary of trying to make life work on your own,

32:45.250 --> 32:50.936
I'd invite you to open your heart to Him, open your heart to Jesus, maybe today's the very first time.

32:50.976 --> 33:01.226
You can pray something like this, not about the right words, we always say that, but these are just, maybe your heart resonates with this, and maybe you're so tired, you can't put words together yourself.

33:02.007 --> 33:03.428
This might be helpful to you.

33:03.548 --> 33:05.350
Jesus, thanks for loving me no matter what.

33:06.631 --> 33:10.215
I realized today how tired I am, trying to make life work on my own.

33:12.037 --> 33:13.298
I really need you.

33:16.578 --> 33:17.999
I need you to forgive my sin.

33:18.019 --> 33:19.961
I need you to fill me with your spirit.

33:20.582 --> 33:26.147
I need you and want to follow your leadership in my life from this day forward.

33:30.391 --> 33:34.015
Maybe you're so tired, that seems like too many words.

33:38.159 --> 33:39.820
Maybe for you it's just help me Jesus.

33:42.863 --> 33:43.123
Help me.

33:45.546 --> 33:46.066
Let's pray.

33:48.162 --> 33:51.527
Lord, thank you for my friends who made it a priority to be here today.

33:52.668 --> 34:00.479
And I pray that you will absolutely maximize your truth in their hearts and in their lives and their spirits today.

34:02.182 --> 34:14.739
I pray for any in the room who may be resonated with that prayer, and it's the very first time they have ever called out to you to be their forgiver, opened their hearts to you as their leader.

34:15.701 --> 34:16.722
Thank you for hearing them.

34:17.250 --> 34:18.752
Thank you for responding to that.

34:20.133 --> 34:25.599
You always promise to respond to every prayer for deliverance, salvation, forgiveness, healing.

34:26.661 --> 34:30.365
And so thank you for hearing them.

34:30.385 --> 34:39.615
And I want to pray for your kids, Lord, that are in this room who've been following you for a long time and they're in a season.

34:41.477 --> 34:42.258
They're in a season.

34:43.650 --> 34:47.115
And it's dragged on longer than any other season they've ever had in their lives.

34:48.837 --> 34:51.080
And it's stretching their trust muscle.

34:53.484 --> 34:59.833
It's stretching them and their ability to stay positive and stay hopeful.

35:01.976 --> 35:03.057
I'm so glad they're here today.

35:05.180 --> 35:08.064
And I know you're glad they're here.

35:08.084 --> 35:12.210
And I pray that you would refresh and revive them

35:12.834 --> 35:14.576
through the power and presence of your spirit.

35:15.518 --> 35:17.240
Strengthen them in their inner being.

35:18.902 --> 35:22.487
Give them everything they need to continue to step forward.

35:23.668 --> 35:27.173
Full of hope, even though they're weary.

35:29.536 --> 35:30.357
Full of hope in you.

35:32.821 --> 35:36.325
So I push them into your lap, Lord Jesus, our tender shepherd.

35:39.610 --> 35:41.072
In your name, amen.

35:42.213 --> 35:42.834
All right.

35:44.162 --> 35:46.345
So, glad you came to church.

35:47.346 --> 35:48.428
Isaiah 40, huh?

35:49.530 --> 35:51.873
Yeah, read it, live it, love it.

35:52.273 --> 35:54.877
All right, stand up with me as we prepare to go.

35:55.698 --> 36:02.688
And if you came today prepared to worship through the giving of your tithes and offerings, the black boxes are by the wall on your way out, just like to remind you of that.

36:02.768 --> 36:04.470
Otherwise, greet one another as you go.

36:04.531 --> 36:05.692
Maybe meet a new person.

36:05.732 --> 36:06.834
It's nice weather out there.

36:07.595 --> 36:09.858
Meet a new friend, greet an old one.

36:11.140 --> 36:11.741
Have a great week.

36:12.021 --> 36:12.722
See you back next time.

